Phlox terry Chanel, Plazmas /
100% double flowers /
Marked with the sign of the Quality of Flora-Select (Fleuroselect Quality), which is awarded to varieties that showed themselves very reliable and have new quality characteristics. If you want to hear admiring reviews of your guests, plant this plant along the tracks or plant a separate group on the lawn. This compact, abundantly flowering plant, with a height of 25 - 30 cm, is all covered with double gently pink flowers (up to 3 cm in diameter). Numerous flowers are collected in large corymbose inflorescences. Unlike many varieties of perennial phlox, flowers do not burn out in the sun. Used for framing flower beds, decorating balcony boxes, creating curbs along the tracks, it will look great in the group on the lawn. It can also be grown as a potted plant in a roomy environment.
/
Agrotechnics of cultivation /
Sowing: for seedlings in March, or in open ground in April-May. After the appearance of two real leaves seedlings dive. In the open ground seedlings are planted in May, the distance between plants is 20 cm. They prefer sunny places. It grows well and blooms on light, nutritious soils. Do not place the phlox on a fresh manure fertilizer. /
Care: in dry weather, watering is required, otherwise bloom is deteriorating. Raw weather and stagnation of soil water tolerate poorly. For better tillering it is recommended to hold a pin on the fourth or fifth pair of leaves.
Flowering: abundant from the end of May to frost, when grown in seedlings. Or from July to frost when poev straight into the open ground.

The basis of shampoos - saponified oils (cedar, coconut, castor), enriched with extracts of healthy hair for herbs and plants. /
Saponification is the process of splitting oil or fat alkali into the original constituents. In this case, the released fatty acids react with alkali and form salts of fatty acids, which we call soap. It is thanks to the saponified oils that the shampoo foams and has detergent properties. /
Shampoos do not contain silicone, weighting hair, and parabens. As a preservative used colloidal silver - a solution of microscopic particles of silver. Possesses preservative, disinfectant, antibacterial properties, reduces irritation. /
